The paper discusses the use of deep neural networks for speech recognition, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). The paper also mentions the use of statistical mechanical theory to understand the network's behavior, which suggests a focus on the theoretical aspects of machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.SD (machine learning), followed by cs.CL (computation and language), cs.LG (learning), cs.NE (neural and evolutionary computing), and cs.SY (systems and control).
